==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obsignation
<hw>Ob`sig*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>obsignatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of sealing or ratifying; the
state of being sealed or confirmed; confirmation, as by the Holy
Spirit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The spirit of manifestation will but upbraid you in the shame and
horror of a sad eternity, if you have not the spirit of
<qex>obsignation</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obsignatory</ent>⟦br⟧
